               <p>LUCY PENDRILL. I am a <rs id="t18280221-297-viclabel1568" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-297-victim1655 t18280221-297-viclabel1568"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280221-297-crimeloc1569">Angel-street, St. Martin's-le-grand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-297-crimeloc1569" type="placeName" value="Angel-street, St. Martin's-le-grand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-297-crimeloc1569" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-297-off1566 t18280221-297-crimeloc1569"></join>. On the 31st of January my two boys were playing in my shop - one of them called Stop thief! and the prisoner was brought back with this boot.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-297-person1656">
                  GEORGE 
                  PENDRILL
               <interp inst="t18280221-297-person1656" type="surname" value="PENDRILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-297-person1656" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-297-person1656" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in my mother's shop, and saw the prisoner come in and take a boot off the shelf - I called Stop thief! he dropped it, and ran away; I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-297-person1657">
                  HEZEKIAH 
                  WILMER
               <interp inst="t18280221-297-person1657" type="surname" value="WILMER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-297-person1657" type="given" value="HEZEKIAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-297-person1657" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . About seven o'clock on the 31st of January, I saw the prisoner at the corner of this window, and soon after heard a cry of Stop thief! I ran back, and took the prisoner, who was running from the shop; the boy said he had taken the boot.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
